         <OBJECT_CONTRACT>
            <TITLE>
               <P>Develop a UK-China Joint Research and Innovation Centre (JRIC) joint venture and associated programme</P>
            </TITLE>
            <REFERENCE_NUMBER>TRN 1449/03/2018</REFERENCE_NUMBER>
            <CPV_MAIN>
               <CPV_CODE CODE="73300000"/>
            </CPV_MAIN>
            <TYPE_CONTRACT CTYPE="SERVICES"/>
            <SHORT_DESCR>
               <P>BEIS commissioned the National Nuclear Laboratory (NNL) for developing a UK-China Joint Research and Innovation Centre (JRIC) joint venture and associated programme, together with the costs of transitioning that model into the current non-JV approach being managed by the Nuclear Innovation and Research Office (NIRO). Note that BEIS commissioned NNL to complete this work (rather than pursuant to a formal contract). BEIS is paying NNL’s incurred costs since this programme commenced in November 2016.</P>
               <P>These costs include, but are not limited to: external legal and financial advice, developing technical work streams, communications and implementation. The work of the NIRO after March 2018 has been included in the business case for the delivery of the JRIC collaborative programme, to be approved by the BEIS Energy Innovation Portfolio Board.</P>
            </SHORT_DESCR>
            <VAL_TOTAL CURRENCY="GBP">300000</VAL_TOTAL>
            <NO_LOT_DIVISION/>
            <OBJECT_DESCR ITEM="1">
               <n2016:NUTS CODE="UK"/>
               <MAIN_SITE>
                  <P>UNITED KINGDOM.</P>
               </MAIN_SITE>
               <SHORT_DESCR>
                  <P>BEIS commissioned NNL for developing a UK-China JRIC joint venture and associated programme, together with the costs of transitioning that model into the current non-JV approach being managed by the NIRO. BEIS is paying NNL’s incurred costs since this was established in November 2016.</P>
               </SHORT_DESCR>
               <NO_OPTIONS/>
               <NO_EU_PROGR_RELATED/>
            </OBJECT_DESCR>
         </OBJECT_CONTRACT>
         <PROCEDURE>
            <DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
               <PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL>
                  <D_OUTSIDE_SCOPE/>
                  <D_JUSTIFICATION>
                     <P>The appointment of The National Nuclear Laboratory (NNL), a Government-owned facility set up as a result of there being no other provider of the broad-ranging independent advice required on nuclear R&amp;D issues, is made under Regulation 32 (2) (b) (ii), (ii) and (9) of the UK’s.</P>
                     <P>Public Contracts Regulations 2015 (negotiated procedure without notice).</P>
                     <P>It has a strategic role to act on behalf of UK Government in an independent and authoritative way and is uniquely qualified to provide wholly independent advice to Government. BEIS is to fund payment of National Nuclear Laboratory (NNL)’s costs incurred, and its projected costs to be incurred until 31.3.2018, in respect of work undertaken on the creation of the UK-China Nuclear Joint Research and Innovation Centre (JRIC). Future work will now be undertaken by the Nuclear Innovation Research Office (NIRO) to provide advisory support to BEIS and China Atomic Energy Agency (CAEA) so changing the JRIC programme structure and funding approach allowing a more common international collaborative programme delivery mode without the need for a formal Joint Venture.</P>
                  </D_JUSTIFICATION>
               </PT_AWARD_CONTRACT_WITHOUT_CALL>
            </DIRECTIVE_2014_24_EU>
